briefdescription.para: Initializes the DbcStruct with values from the parsed DBC file.

detaileddescription.para: Initializes the DbcStruct for CAN message processing.
This function initializes the necessary fields in the DbcStruct based on the provided DBC messages. The signals' physical factors and offsets are set accordingly.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the DbcStruct instance to be initialized.

briefdescription.para: Reads and parses CAN data into the DbcStruct.

detaileddescription.para: Creates the signal table for the specified CAN message.

This function is used to read CAN data and store it in the DbcStruct. It parses the data and converts physical values to raw CAN signal values based on the scaling factors and offsets defined in the DbcStruct.

rx_data
Pointer to the received CAN data to be parsed.
id
CAN message ID for identifying which message to parse.
dbc
Pointer to the DbcStruct where parsed data will be stored.
Creates the signal table for a specified CAN message in the DbcStruct.
This function initializes the signal table for a specific message within the DbcStruct. Each signal is set to 0 initially, preparing it for further use.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the DbcStruct containing the CAN message and signals.

briefdescription.para: Creates the signal table for the specified CAN message.

detaileddescription.para: This function initializes the signal table for the given CAN message. It organizes and prepares the signals in the message to be ready for processing or encoding.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the DbcStruct instance that contains the CAN message.

briefdescription.para: Converts a physical value to a raw CAN signal value.

detaileddescription.para: Converts a physical value to its corresponding raw CAN value.
This function converts a physical value (e.g., temperature) into a raw CAN signal value based on the scaling factor and offset stored in the Phys_Value_t structure.

parameterdescription.para: Pointer to the Phys_Value_t structure containing scaling factor and offset.

simplesect.para: The corresponding raw CAN signal value.

briefdescription.para: Converts a raw CAN signal value to a physical value.

detaileddescription.para: Converts a raw CAN value to its corresponding physical value.
This function converts a raw CAN signal value to its corresponding physical value based on the scaling factor and offset stored in the Phys_Value_t structure.

parameterdescription.para: The raw CAN signal value to convert.
Pointer to the Phys_Value_t structure containing scaling factor and offset.
